body:
UNBOXING | Metroid Samus Returns amiibo

I heard people complaining about the Samus amiibo when it was first announced. Something about it not being a very exciting pose or something. Plain and boring might have been used? I dunno, I don’t see it!

It’s such a great looking figure. If you’re a fan of the series, you should not be disappointed at all. And the detail in the armor and the cannon is great.

At first glance it may not look…

summary:
Thursday Update：Yokai Watch 4 Delayed, Disaster Report 4 Announced, Super Mario Maker 2 News, Plus Much More！


Please support...
body:
Thursday Update：Yokai Watch 4 Delayed, Disaster Report 4 Announced, Super Mario Maker 2 News, Plus Much More！

Please support me by shopping here
(use JPNINTENDO for $3 USD off)!

● Just three weeks away from launch, Level-5 announced they have delayed the release of their first major Nintendo Switch exclusive Yokai Watch 4: Bokura wa Onajikara o Miage Tale by a fortnight, to 20 June, in order to improve the quality of the finished product.

● Granzella announced Zettai Zetsumei Toshi４Plus – Summer Memories – for Nintendo Switch (Disaster Report 4 Plus: Summer Memories) as coming to Switch this September in Japan. Check out the promo video and box art at this post.

● Check out yesterday’s full Super Mario Maker 2 Nintendo Direct recap and presentation at this post and the website here. The game is available to preload priced at ¥6,458 and requiring 2.8 GB.

● Nintendo announced a Nintendo Catalog Ticket (Nintendo Switch Game Vouchers) promotion for Nintendo Switch Online members who can purchase a set of two vouchers for ¥9,980 that can be used for first-party games including Astral Chain, Fire Emblem: Three Houses, and Super Mario Maker 2. Check out the trailer here.
